"title": "7924: fellowship, in Christian service",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7924: fellowship, in christian service",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Partnership in a common enterprise. God's people are called to work together especially in the task of mission, to recognise one another's gifts and to give support to one another's ministries.</p>\n<h2>Fellowship in mission</h2>\n<h3>Partnership in preaching the gospel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:9\">GAL 2:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:7\">MRK 10:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:1-Luke10:2\">LUK 10:1–10:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:5\">PHP 1:5</a></p>\n<h3>Supporting the work of others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:26\">ACT 14:26</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:14-Phil4:16\">PHP 4:14–4:16</a></strong> <em>The Philippians share in Paul's work through their giving.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:2-Acts13:3\">ACT 13:2–13:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:40\">ACT 15:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:9\">2CO 11:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/3John1:5-3John1:8\">3JN 1:5–1:8</a></p>\n<h3>Standing together in adversity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:32-Heb10:34\">HEB 10:32–10:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor1:7\">2CO 1:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:27-Phil1:30\">PHP 1:27–1:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:14\">PHP 4:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:25\">HEB 11:25</a></p>\n<h3>Fellowship between Paul and his co-workers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:3\">PHP 4:3</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:26-Acts11:30\">ACT 11:26–11:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:42-Acts13:50\">ACT 13:42–13:50</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:1-Acts14:23\">ACT 14:1–14:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:22-Acts15:29\">ACT 15:22–15:29</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:3\">ROM 16:3</a> <em>Priscilla and Aquila</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:9\">ROM 16:9</a> <em>Urbanus</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:21\">ROM 16:21</a> <em>Timothy</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor8:23\">2CO 8:23</a> <em>Titus</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:25\">PHP 2:25</a> <em>Epaphroditus</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phlm1:1\">PHM 1:1</a> <em>Philemon</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phlm1:24\">PHM 1:24</a> <em>Mark, Aristarchus, Demas and Luke</em></p>\n<h2>In fellowship different gifts are combined for effective service</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:12\">1CO 12:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:4-1Cor12:6\">1CO 12:4–12:6</a></p>\n<h3>Spiritual gifts are given to all to share</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:7\">1CO 12:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:4-Rom12:8\">ROM 12:4–12:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:14-1Cor12:20\">1CO 12:14–12:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:10\">1PE 4:10</a></p>\n<h3>Recognising one another's gifts</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:21-1Cor12:26\">1CO 12:21–12:26</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Accepting one another's ministries</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:7-Gal2:8\">GAL 2:7–2:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:27-1Cor12:31\">1CO 12:27–12:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor16:15-1Cor16:18\">1CO 16:15–16:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:15-2Pet3:16\">2PE 3:15–3:16</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of sharing in different roles</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh4:16-Neh4:22\">NEH 4:16–4:22</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:5-1Cor3:8\">1CO 3:5–3:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:15-Exod4:16\">EXO 4:15–4:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod17:10-Exod17:13\">EXO 17:10–17:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:8-1Cor12:11\">1CO 12:8–12:11</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of working together in fellowship</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl4:9-Eccl4:12\">ECC 4:9–4:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut3:18-Deut3:20\">DEU 3:18–3:20</a> <em>the Reubenites and the Gadites join with the rest of Israel to conquer Canaan</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg20:11\">JDG 20:11</a> <em>all Israel unites against Gibeah</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra3:8-Ezra3:10\">EZR 3:8–3:10</a> <em>Those returning from exile work together to rebuild the temple</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh4:6\">NEH 4:6</a> <em>The Israelites work together to rebuild the walls of Jerusalem</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:7-Luke5:10\">LUK 5:7–5:10</a> <em>Peter and Andrew, James and John are business partners.</em></p>",
